verse.lines:
{lang-eng}O Lord my God, when I in awesome wonder,
Consider all the works Thy hand hath made,
I see the stars; I hear the mighty thunder;
Thy power throughout the universe displayed;{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Then sings my soul, my Savior God, to
Thee,
How great Thou art!  How great Thou art!{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}And when I think: that God, His Son not sparing,
Sent Him to die – I scarce can take it in;
That on the cross, my burden gladly bearing,
He bled and died, to take away my sin.{/lang-eng}
